This article is a Presidential Proclamation by President Barack Obama declaring Memorial Day, May 27, 2013, as a day of prayer for permanent peace. The President pays tribute to the patriots who have served and fought for the country, emphasizing the sacrifices they made for their families and their love for America. He calls on Americans to honor the fallen by living up to the ideals they died defending and by meeting obligations to veterans and their families. The President also highlights the importance of preserving liberty, advancing justice, and working towards peace. He requests the flag to be flown at half-staff until noon on Memorial Day and asks Americans to observe the National Moment of Remembrance at 3:00 p.m. local time. The proclamation concludes with President Obama's signature.